The main duties and responsibilities of the Program Assistant are as following:
1. Manage administrative, logistics and financial affairs of Integrity centre; 
2. Identify and mapping civil society organizations/ CSOs;
3. Share the published resources with CSOs and other stakeholders;
4. Maintain and update all project records, files and database;
5. Equip the Integrity Center with soft and hard resources/ documents concerning anti-corruption, social accountability, and access to information;
6. Prepare and compile activity reports and submit to Integrity Building Program on regular basis;
7. Liaise with CSOs, NGOs, UN agencies and other stakeholders to establish and maintain coordination networks;
8. Represent Integrity Watch in all coordination meetings at the provincial level;
9. Prepare weekly and monthly work plans and sharing with Integrity Building Program Manager;
10. Develop and present progress reports to Integrity Building Program Manager;
11. Hold meetings with stakeholders including citizen groups, academia (public policy departments of universities) and encourage them to use the facilities of the Integrity Center;
12. Coordinate with CSOs and government on anti-corruption efforts;
13. Assist the Provincial Coordinator/field officer in financial and logistics tasks;
14. Assist in establishing Provincial Integrity Networks/ PINs as knowledge platform to influence local authorities demand integrity and fight against corruption.

